sage\navg_memory_usage = statistics.mean(memory_usages)\n\n# Identify consistent high-memory models and OOM errors\nhigh_usage_models = [model for model in memory_usages if model > 90]\noom_error_times = oom_errors\n\nprint(f\"Average GPU Memory Usage: {avg_memory_usage}%\")\nprint(f\"Consistent High-Usage Models: {high_usage_models}\")\nprint(f\"OOM Errors at Times: {oom_error_times}\")\n\n# Recommendations\nif avg_memory_usage > 90:\n    print(\"Consider increasing GPU memory.\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Current memory usage is within acceptable limits.\")\n\n# Optimize model usage patterns and set concurrency limits\nconcurrency_limit = min(4, len(high_usage_models))\nprint(f\"Recommended Concurrency Limit for High-Usage Models: {concurrency_limit}\")\n```\n\nWould you like to proceed with implementing these recommendations or gather more detailed data from your actual logs?",
