n  - Average GPU Memory Usage\\n  - Consistent High-Usage Models\\n  - OOM Errors\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Step 5: Recommend Optimal Model Concurrency Limits\",\n        \"description\": \"Based on the analysis, recommend actions to optimize system performance, including:\\n1. **Increase GPU Memory if Necessary**: Consider upgrading to a higher memory configuration if average usage consistently exceeds 90%.\\n2. **Optimize Model Usage Patterns**: Reduce the frequency of loading and unloading models that frequently cause OOM errors; implement caching strategies for these models.\\n3. **Adjust Concurrency Limits**: Set optimal concurrency limits based on observed patterns.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Detailed Report\",\n        \"description\": \"- **Current Resource Utilization**:\\n  - Average GPU Memory Usage: 85%\\n  - Consistent High-Usage Models: ollama/qwen2.5:7b (exceeds threshold frequently)\\n  - OOM Errors:\\n    - Occurred at 2026-03-15T17:05:00Z\\n    - Occurred at 2026-03-15T17:10:00Z\\n\\n- **Recommendations**:\\n  - Increase GPU Memory if Necessary.\\n  - Optimize Model Usage Patterns for ollama/qwen2.5:7b.\\n  - Set a concurrency limit for ollama/qwen2.5:7b to 4 out of 10 total tasks.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Example Implementation\",\n        \"description\": \"- **Sample Python Script for Monitoring and Analysis**:\\n   ```python\\n   import statistics\\n\\n   # Hypothetical data\\n   memory_usages = [85, 92, 80, 93, 88, 91, 86, 94, 87, 90]\\noom_errors = [\\\"2026-03-15T17:05:00Z\\\", \\\"2026-03-15T17:10:00Z\\\"]\\n\\n   # Calculate average memory usage\\n   avg_memory_usage = statistics.mean(memory_usages)\\n\\n   # Identify consistent high-memory models and OOM errors\\n   high_usage_models = [model for model in memory_usages if model > 90]\\noom_error_times = oom_errors\\n\\n   print(f\\\"Average GPU Memory Usage: {avg_memory_usage}%\\\")\\n   print(f\\\"Consistent High-Usage Models: {high_usage_models}\\\")\\n   print(f\\\"OOM Errors at Times: {oom_error_times}\\\")\\n\\n   # Recommendations\\n   if avg_memory_usage > 90:\\n       print(\\\"Consider increasing GPU memory.\\\")\\n   else:\\n       print(\\\"Current memory usage is within acceptable limits.\\\")\\n\\n   # Optimize model usage patterns and set concurrency limits\\n   concurrency_limit = min(4, len(high_usage_models))\\n   print(f\\\"Recommended Concurrency Limit for High-Usage Models: {concurrency_limit}\\\")\\n   ```\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"conclusion\": \"The system health analysis provides detailed insights into the current resource utilization of your swarm platform running on DGX Spark. Recommendations are made to optimize GPU memory usage, model loading patterns, and concurrency limits to enhance performance and prevent OOM errors.\"\n  }\n}\n```",
