efined dependencies between sub-tasks available.\\n- **Steps**:\\n  1. Input complex task with defined dependencies to coordinator.\\n  2. Coordinator generates dependency graph and checks for cycles.\\n\\n- **Expected Outcome**:\\n  - Dependencies are accurately defined, and no cycles exist in the graph.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"3. Critic Review Accuracy\",\n        \"description\": \"Verify that critics provide accurate and useful reviews of completed sub-tasks.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Test Case: Critic Review Accuracy\",\n        \"description\": \"- **Scenario**: Comprehensive review of completed sub-tasks.\\n- **Preconditions**: Specialists complete tasks, and critics are available.\\n- **Steps**:\\n  1. Input completed sub-tasks to critic.\\n  2. Critics provide detailed reviews.\\n  3. Coordinator aggregates reviews and integrates them into the final output.\\n\\n- **Expected Outcome**:\\n  - Reviews are comprehensive, addressing all aspects of the sub-task.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"4. Aggregation Completeness\",\n        \"description\": \"Ensure that all sub-tasks and reviews are aggregated correctly to form a complete final output.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Test Case: Aggregation Completeness\",\n        \"description\": \"- **Scenario**: Integration of all sub-tasks and reviews into a complete final document.\\n- **Preconditions**: Specialists and critics have completed their tasks.\\n- **Steps**:\\n  1. Input aggregated outputs from specialists and critics to coordinator.\\n  2. Coordinator checks for completeness and integrates all components.\\n\\n- **Expected Outcome**:\\n  - All components of the task are integrated cohesively without missing any parts.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"5. Error Recovery\",\n        \"description\": \"Test the coordinator's ability to handle errors and recover gracefully.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Test Case: Error Recovery\",\n        \"description\": \"- **Scenario**: Handling task failures and reassigning tasks.\\n- **Preconditions**: Task failure due to an unexpected bug.\\n- **Steps**:\\n  1. Input complex task with defined dependencies and specialists.\\n  2. Specialist C (Coding) fails due to a bug.\\n  3. Coordinator detects the failure, reassigns coding sub-task to another specialist D if available.\\n\\n- **Expected Outcome**:\\n  - The system automatically handles failures, reassigns tasks if necessary, and maintains overall task completion.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Detailed Test Plan\",\n        \"description\": \"- **Test Case 1: Task Decomposition Quality**\\n  - Steps include inputting a complex task, coordinator decomposition, and specialist assignment.\\n- **Test Case 2: Dependency Graph Correctness**\\n  - Steps include inputting dependencies, coordinator graph generation, and cycle detection.\\n- **Test Case 3: Critic Review Accuracy**\\n  - Steps include reviewing completed sub-tasks, aggregating reviews, and integrating final output.\\n- **Test Case 4: Aggregation Completeness**\\n  - Steps include inputting aggregated outputs and checking for completeness.\\n- **Test Case 5: Error Recovery**\\n  - Steps include failure detection, reassignment of tasks, and maintenance of overall completion.\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"conclusion\": \"The comprehensive test plan ensures that the swarm platform's coordinator-specialist pattern operates reliably and effectively. Each test case provides specific scenarios with expected outcomes to validate key aspects of the system.\"\n  }\n}\n```",
